name: 3.Model Training
content:
Model Training :

In this analysis, we are using H2O Distributed Random Forest model, H2O Score and H2O model save for saving the models trained on several selected features. The subsequent sections provide a comprehensive overview of the model's performance on both training and testing datasets.


1.H2O Distributed Random Forest Model :

  • During model training, H2O's DRF uses bagging techniques and parallel processing to ensure both speed and accuracy in handling large datasets.
  • The process includes extensive hyperparameter tuning to optimize performance and minimize overfitting, leading to robust model predictions.
  • This scalable and flexible approach is ideal for various predictive tasks, including both classification and regression.
  • DRF automatically manages different data types, reducing the need for manual preprocessing and making it user-friendly.


2.H2O Score :

  • Provides high accuracy in predictive tasks by leveraging gradient boosting and advanced optimization techniques.
  • During scoring, the model evaluates key metrics such as AUC, F1-score, and RMSE to assess performance.
  • Supports real-time scoring, enabling rapid and efficient predictions on new data as it becomes available.


3.H2O model save :

  • Allows for simple and efficient saving of trained models, facilitating easy storage and transfer.
  • Models can be saved in various formats, such as MOJO (Model Object, Optimized) or POJO (Plain Old Java Object), ensuring compatibility with different deployment environments.
  • The saving process is optimized for large-scale models, ensuring that even complex models can be saved without performance issues.
  • Saved models can be easily reloaded and reused for future predictions, updates, or further training, enhancing workflow efficiency and model lifecycle management.
